<item>
            <title>[PIG-1709] Skewed join use fewer reducer for extreme large key</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1709</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In skewed join, we use PartitionSkewedKeys to calculate number of reducers needed for a single key. If the result if larger than the number of total reducers, we will round it with reducer#. Eg, if Pig calculates that we need 12 reducers to hold a key in memory, and total reducers for this job is 10, we then allocate 2 reducers to this key; We shall use all 10 reducers in this case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
